rComments: The course I took with Liz Alexander was difficult, but anything worth learning is. Prof. Alexander is an excellent teacher. I found she was clear, she forced us to think, and moreover, she always provided concrete and useful feedback on any question asked of her. She encouraged us to work hard and she helped us to produce the best work we could.

Easily the worst prof I have encountered at UofT. She is arrogant. Preaches her interpretations as gospel. Original though is discouraged, while regurgitation of her thoughts is rewarded. Has unreasonable expectations and no respect for students. DO NOT take her class. I do not have one positive thing to say about her. She is an embarrassment.

A complete waste of what sounds like would be an interesting class "Politics and Morality."  Instead, the class seemed like an English class, focussed and centred around Shakespeare's plays.  A total waste of a course.  Her teaching style was less than amusing, and if attending class was not mandatory, I highly doubt most would attend.

Her course on ethics in politics felt more like an English class than a political science class, due to her use of Shakespeare's plays.  She cited the most irrelevant details in that play that had not one iota to do with ethics.
